Subject: [PATCH 0457/1074] ENGR00321599-1 ARM: dts: imx6sx: adjust ARM power
 up timing in gpc

Speed up ARM power up time in GPC to reduce latency of cpu low
power idle exit time.

SW2ISO: set to two 32k clock before negating isolation;
SW    : set to one 32k clock after receiving a power up request.

As the ARM LDO ramp up time is ~40us, so SW2ISO need to be larger
then 40s, here it is set to 2, ~62.5us.

So the total latency of GPC ARM power up is ~93.75us.

Signed-off-by: Anson Huang <b20788@freescale.com>
